Why don’t you ask Corey, the owner and founder of Turbat Lines if he doesn’t have an opinion about this? He will surely tell you. Corey has a Harley Davidson Street Bob bike, another reason being that he just likes big Harleys. There are high chances that you also will like it. The downside of buying a motorcycle in Pakistan is the stress on the parts. For example, the Honda CD 70 is a great bike, but its transmission is quite outdated, and it breaks down regularly.

Buyer’s guide when getting a bike in Pakistan

If you are new to Pakistan, you might need some insights. You should not expect to buy a car or a bike like in other countries if you are visiting for the first time. Try to get a used bike from the local market. This way, you can use that bike to get to places in Pakistan and in case of any miscalculations, they are not your problem. If you don’t like the bike, you can sell it. Promoting bikes is pretty easy in Pakistan. Cheap fees and a lot of buyers are all you need. But with returning customers, you know you did well.
